## Database Setup

### {{ database_type | title }}

{% if database_type == 'postgresql' %}
1. Install PostgreSQL
2. Create database:
   ```sql
   CREATE DATABASE {{ project_name | snake_case }};
   ```
3. Update configuration in `config.{% if config_format %}{{ config_format }}{% else %}json{% endif %}` with your database credentials
{% elif database_type == 'mysql' %}
1. Install MySQL
2. Create database:
   ```sql
   CREATE DATABASE {{ project_name | snake_case }};
   ```
3. Update configuration in `config.{% if config_format %}{{ config_format }}{% else %}json{% endif %}` with your database credentials
{% elif database_type == 'mongodb' %}
1. Install MongoDB
2. Start MongoDB server
3. Database will be created automatically on first use
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

## Configuration

{% if has_config_file %}
The application uses {{ config_format | upper }} for configuration. Edit `config.{{ config_format }}` to customize:

{% if config_format == 'json' %}
```json
{
  "application": {
    "name": "{{ project_name }}",
    "version": "{{ project_version }}"
  }{% if has_logging %},
  "logging": {
    "level": "{{ log_level }}",
    "file": "logs/{{ project_name | snake_case }}.log"
  }{% endif %}{% if has_database %},
  "database": {
    "type": "{{ database_type }}"
  }{% endif +%}
}
```
{% elif config_format == 'yaml' %}
```yaml
application:
  name: {{ project_name }}
  version: {{ project_version }}
{% if has_logging %}
logging:
  level: {{ log_level }}
  file: logs/{{ project_name | snake_case }}.log
{% endif %}
{% if has_database %}
database:
  type: {{ database_type }}
{% endif %}
```
{% endif %}
{% else %}
Configuration is managed through code. See `src/config.py` for details.
{% endif %}

